WhatsApp is rolling out an update for Stickers support, according to a report by WABetaInfo. The feature will work on Android and iOS initially. WhatsApp will support Facebook Sticker packs, and in the future Stickers submitted by third parties. 12 Stickers packs are being rolled out, added the report, including Cuppy by Minseung Song, Salty by Alisa Kryzhanovska, and Komo by Sanat Rath. While the packs only include static Stickers, animated Stickers will be available in the near future. “To send Stickers, you need to tap the Stickers button, located on the chat bar on iOS and on the keyboard on Android.